The '''Supreme Electoral Council''' ({{lang-es|Consejo Supremo Electoral}}, CSE) is an autonomous, public organization responsible for organizing elections in [[Nicaragua]]. 

Roberto Rivas Reyes has been president of the CSE since July 2000,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.laprensa.com.ni/2017/01/11/politica/2163335-roberto-rivas-estoy-bien-donde-estoy|title=Roberto Rivas: “Yo estoy bien donde estoy”|last=Álvarez|first=Leonor|date=2017-01-11|work=La Prensa|access-date=2018-05-06|language=es-ES}}</ref> though as of January 2018, vice-president [[Lumberto Campbell]] functioned as acting head of the organization.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.havanatimes.org/?p=130137|title=No Official in Nicaragua Wants to Investigate Roberto Rivas|last=Miranda Aburto|first=Wilfredo|date=January 29, 2018|website=www.havanatimes.org|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-05-07}}</ref>

